Now, $[ACDE] = \frac{3}{10}=[CBDE]$ so $DE$ is parallel to $AB$ and $[ADE] : [BCE] = 3 : 4$. Consider triangles $AFD$ and $CFE$. We have $\angle ADF = \angle CEF$ and $\angle DAF = \angle ECF$ so the triangles are similar by AA similarity. So $\frac{EF}{FA} = \frac{2}{5}.$</think> <answer> <solution>$[BCDE] = \frac{7}{2}[ADE],$ so $BC:DE = 7:2.$ Also, $\angle ADB = \angle ADC$ and $\angle BAD = \angle CAD$, so $\triangle ABD \sim \triangle ACB$. Therefore, $AD:CD = AB:AC = 1:5$ and $CD = 2 \cdot 5 = 10$, so $BD:CD = 1:5$, and $DE:BC = 1:7$. So we can draw the following similar triangles: \begin{align*}
\triangle AFE \sim \triangle CDE \\
\triangle AFE \sim \triangle BCA \\
ADE \sim CDE
\end{align*} So \begin{align*}
\frac{FE}{DA} &= \frac{DE}{CE} = \frac{1}{7} \Rightarrow FE = \frac{DA}{7} = \frac{3}{7} 
FE:FA &= DA:AC = 3:15 = 1:5 \Rightarrow FA = 5 \cdot \frac{3}{7} = \frac{15}{7} \Rightarrow \frac{EF}{FA} = \frac{3}{15} = \boxed{\frac{1}{5}}.
\end{align*}</solution>

